JOHANNESBURG - Mark Scott-Crossley made a brief appearance in the Lenyenye Magistrate's Court in Tzaneen, Limpopo on Friday.Scott-Crossley is accused of attempted murder in another apparent racially motivated attack.Silence Mabunda brought charges against him, saying he was attacked while buying airtime at a shop.He has accused Scott-Crossley of driving over him.Scott-Crossley is expected to make his first appearance in the Hoedspruit Magistrate's Court today.He made international headlines in 2004, for killing an employee by pushing him into a lions' den.He was released on parole in 2008.Scott Crossley will be remanded in custody and a formal bail application will be heard on Monday, 30 January. AFP